<paragraph blockId="10.[170,777,1731,2091]" lastBlockId="10.[813,1182,160,185]" pageId="10" pageNumber="193">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[171,333,1731,1755]" pageId="10" pageNumber="193">Identification.</emphasis>
Characterized by dichotomous, usually prostrate, non-articulate stems with 4 ranks of leaves: two lateral rows of larger spreading leaves and two rows of appressed and ascending median leaves on upper side of stem. Sporangia globose, opening by a slit across the top, arranged in quadrangular strobili located terminally on axes. Plants heterosporous, the megaspores four per sporangium, white, the microspores numerous per sporangium, orange. 
<taxonomicName box="[406,634,2000,2024]" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Sellaginella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Selaginellales" pageId="10" pageNumber="193" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis box="[406,634,2000,2024]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="193">Sellaginella flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other species of the genus in the area by oblong to elliptic lateral leaves, aristate median leaves, and a somewhat rugose texture of leaves adaxially.
</paragraph>
